{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The plane has been connected to the jetbridge. The aircraft door is open. Unload baggages.", 
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Unload baggages.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        class = "ollama"
        temperature = 0.0
        model_name = "qwen2.5:32b"  # “gemini-3.1-pro" "gemma4:12b-mlx" "qwen3:8b" "claude-haiku-4-5" "claude-sonnet-4-6"  
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "aicraft_baggage_unload_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
 I am in charge of unloading baggage from the aircraft at the gate. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },       
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connection. Null on stairtruck gates."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of stairtruck connection. Null on jetway gates."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type at the gate (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of aircraft door opening."
                        },         
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of unloading baggages from aircraft.
When user submits inquiry, proceed as follows:
1. Determine if the following are provided: jetbridge_connection_status or
   stairtruck_connection_status, door_opening_status, flight_status,
   deplaning_equipment_type.
2. Call TrackerAPI with all available parameters to get the latest values.
   Wait for its response and store all available parameters.
3. Determine equipment readiness based on deplaning_equipment_type:
   - If deplaning_equipment_type contains 'jetway' or 'jetbridge':
       Equipment is ready if jetbridge_connection_status contains 'connected'.
   - If deplaning_equipment_type contains 'stairtruck' or 'stair':
       Equipment is ready if stairtruck_connection_status contains 'connected'.
   - If deplaning_equipment_type is unknown:
       Accept either connection status as sufficient.
   If equipment is ready AND door_opening_status includes 'open': go to step 6.
4. If equipment is NOT connected:
   - For jetway gate: call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_jetbridge_connect.
   - For stairtruck gate: call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_stairtruck_connect
     with flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
     acu_connection_status, gpu_connection_status.
   Wait for response. Return to step 2.
5. If door_opening_status does not include 'open':
   Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_door_opening with:
     flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
     deplaning_equipment_type,
     jetbridge_connection_status, stairtruck_connection_status.
   Wait for response. Return to step 2.
6. Equipment is connected and door is open.
   Call baggage_unload_operator with:
     flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
     jetbridge_connection_status, stairtruck_connection_status,
     door_opening_status.
   Wait for its response and save it as baggage_unload_status.
7. Call TrackerAPI to store baggage_unload_status.
   Wait for its response and store all available parameters.
8. Provide the baggage unload status report summary as:
    **************************************
    * Summary of aircraft baggage unload *
    **************************************
    ** flight status                 **: [flight_status]
    ** deplaning equipment type      **: [deplaning_equipment_type]
    ** jetbridge connection status   **: [jetbridge_connection_status]
    ** stairtruck connection status  **: [stairtruck_connection_status]
    ** door opening status           **: [door_opening_status]
    ** baggage unload status         **: [baggage_unload_status]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "baggage_unload_status": true
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "gate_id": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true
                        "door_opening_status": true
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "gate_id": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true
                        "door_opening_status": true
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "gate_id": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true
                        "door_opening_status": true
                        "baggage_unload_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["TrackerAPI","baggage_unload_operator","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_door_opening","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_jetbridge_connect","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_stairtruck_connect"]
        },

        {
            "name": "baggage_unload_operator",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent unloads baggages from the aircraft. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connection. Null on stairtruck gates."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of stairtruck connection. Null on jetway gates."
                        },
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of aircraft door opening."
                        },   
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        },         
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_baggage_unload.aircraft_baggage_unload.baggage_unload_operator" 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check jetbridge connection status as jetbridge_connection_status. 
I check door opening status as door_opening_status. 
I check baggage unload status as baggage_unload_status. 
I check stairtruck connection status as stairtruck_connection_status. 
I check deplaning equipment type as deplaning_equipment_type. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },    
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the stairtruck connection status."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_baggage_unload.aircraft_baggage_unload.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}



